						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">byuu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Okay, then I don't personally care. I don't bother with bootleg stuff at all.<br />Even if that means no Gauntlet, it's better than having to defend not supporting Wisdom Tree games.</div>
<br />The Color Dreams board is functionally GNROM with the nibbles swapped and 4 bits of CHR ROM bank address instead of 2. That's all.
<br />
<br />I may be repeating something I said several pages ago, but if you make an emulator that can run games licensed by Nintendo but can't run homebrew, then you run the risk of a judge finding that your emulator doesn't have a "substantial non-infringing use".</div>

