				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I have nothing against getting licensed games to run correctly, just against shunning homebrew games (which are and will forever be unlicensed, since Nintendo doesn't license NES games anymore, no matter how good they are) in the process.
<br />
<br />I find the idea that "only licenced games are relevant" really stupid because licensing games doesn't even have anything to do with how good they are, it has obviously always been about Nintendo making money. Nintendo probably thought that developers who couldn't afford their demands probably couldn't make good games, but this didn't really work as a form of quality control, since there is a lot of licensed crap and a few unlicensed gems out there...
<br />
<br />And I strongly believe that NES homebrewers will be more and more active from now on, releasing really good games (hopefully we'll get past the "single screen puzzle game" for good sometime soon - don't get me wrong, some of these are really cool and addicting, but they still can't compete with the top NES titles) that will help keep the NES alive, so I find it really sad when I see emulator developers, specially talented ones like byuu, not caring about that.</div>

